INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 2,'Phalacrocoracidae', '116::117', 'World: 34 species, SE Asia: 5 species. Large, mostly black. Body egg-shaped. Neck long. Bill end slightly enlarged, curved, sharp. Wings short, broad, round. Feet webbed. Flight strong and direct with outstretched neck, giving a distintive sihouette. Good swimmers and divers, but walk on ground with difficulty. Swim with bill tilled upward, sometimes with only head above surface. Roost and nest in colonies in trees. Often perch with wings outstretched. Gregarious, sexes alike. Cormorants have long bill with hook at tip. Darters have more slender neck, pointed & narrow bill, longer & fan-shaped tail.', ' ');
