INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 1,'Guttifereae', '196', 'Synonym: ''Clusiaceae''. Considered by some authors to be synonymous to ''Hypericaceae''. World 40 genera, 350+ species.<br><br>EVERGREEN. A family of immense importance to forestry. Woody plants or shrubs with resin canals containing YELLOW OR YELLOW-GREEN MILKY LATEX. Branches usually horizontal. Leaves LEATHERY, OPPOSITE or whorled, entire; venations of NUMEROUS fine PARALLEL nerves at RIGHT ANGLE to mid-rib. No stipule. Flowers regular, mono- or bi-sexual; sepals 2-6 in decussate; petals 2-6 contorted; stamens many. Style usually 1. Ovary 1-5-12 celled; stigmas as many as cells in ovary. Fruit usually dehisce, often a berry. Seeds large.<br><br>Habitat: tropical, common in evergreen, semi-evergreen and wet mixed forests.', ' ');
