INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 1,'Amaranthaceae', '246::247', 'World: 65 genera, 900 species; Vietnam: 10 genera, 26 species. Scarcely separable from family ''Chenopodiaceae'', with which it was united by French botanist Baillon. Differs in having perianth dry, membranous, often white or colored, not green and herbaceous as in ''Chenopodiaceae''. Herbs, seldom shrubs, often highly-colored. Leaves opposite or alternate, simple, no stipule. Flowers small, in capitula or spikes, showy, similar in structure with those of ''Chenopodiaceae''. Each flower forms only 1 seed. Most grow wild, somes planted as vegetables or ornaments.<br><br>Distr.: mainly tropics and sub-tropics of Americas & Africa, parts of Asia, few in Europe.', ' ');
