INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 1,'Meliaceae', '343::344', 'World 50 genera, 1,400 species; Vietnam: about 15 genera, 70 species.<br><br>Trees or shrubs. A very important family in forestry, some yield excellent timber and furniture wood species and so planted in plantations in India. Leaves alternate, pinnate; leaflets oblique at base; no stipule. Flowers regular, bisexual, in panicled cymes. Sepals & petals 3-6; stamens as many or twice as many; disc prominent. Overy 3- to 5-celled, generally 2 in each cell. Fruit a drupe, capsule or berry. Seeds often arillate. Next to ''Lauraceae'' in adundance in India.<br><br>Distr.: all over tropics & sub-tropics except arid tracts; some in temperate.', ' ');
