INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 2,'Clupeidae', '540::541', 'About 50 genera, many species. Body roundish or flat from side to side. Head also flat from side to side. Snout does not protrude clearly. Mouth large; teeth small or weak, or absent. Ventral ledge either round or sharp and serrate, sometimes with spine. No lateral line. Scales round, fall off easily. Dorsal fin in middle of body length. Anal fin often long. Caudal fin deeply lobed. Pectoral fin attached low. Some shoals very large. Distr: wide, from tropics, sub-tropics to temperate. Habitat: both freshwater & marine. An important family in marine fishery.', ' ');
