INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 2,'Laniidae', '558::559', 'World: 72 species, SE Asia: 7 species; Thailand: 5 species. Medium-sized, large head, strong and hooked bill, long tail. Prey on insects, rodents, frogs, lizards, small birds... by pouncing on them from an exposed perch, frequently a fence post or telephone wire. Prey often impaled on thorns; hence another name, butcherbird. Often prefer open country. Songs often musical. Have harsh, scolding calls. Solitary and territorial, even in winter quarters. Build bulky, cup-shaped nests placed in tall bushes and low trees.<br><br>TRUE SHRIKES: 25 species of genus ''Lanius'', constituting subfamily ''Laniinae''. Gray or brownish, often with black or white markings. Several Eurasian species have reddish or brown markings. Solitary birds. Harsh calls.', ' ');
