INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 1,'Ebenaceae', '568', 'World: 7 genera, about 450 species; Vietnam: only 2 genera ''Diospyros'' & ''Maba'', 52 species in 71 species of Indochina. Syn.: ''Ebenaceae''. Evolved from family ''Styracaceae''.<br><br>Trees or shrubs. Leaves seldom opposite. Buds formed by young leaves on top of each other, long, with shiny hairs. Flowers MONO-SEXUAL, often DIOECIOUS. Male flowers in cymes axillary; female ones often solitary. Calyx of 3-6 lobes, persistent. Corolla 3-7 lobes, fused or twisted. Stamens as many as petals. Fruit berry, more or less succulent. Seeds with a thin testa. Wood often hard, black, precious.<br><br>Distr.: Old World (not in Australia) & N Americas.', ' ');
