INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 2,'Pittidae', '570::571', 'World: 29 species. Thailand: 12 species. 15-27 cm. Faintly resemble thrushes. All with plump body, stub tail, long legs, short neck, stout bill.  birds. Have an erect carriage; a characteristic bounding gait. Many brilliantly colored. Sexes may be alike or unlike. Usually secretive, shy, difficult to observe, best detected by diagnostic calls, usually of a trill or a short whistle. Wings make a noisy whirring in flight. Move rapidly in long hops, foraging for insects and snails in ground litter; some smash snails, using stones or exposed tree roots as anvils.<br><br>Distr.: most species in Indo-Malayan region, some ranging to the Solomon Islands; 4 occur in Australia, 2 in Africa. Habitat: forest or scrubland, terrestrial. Build domed nests (tend to be large and roughly made) of sticks, leaves, grass, placed on ground or near ground in understory trees or palms.', ' ');
