INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 2,'Sylviidae', '577::578', 'Intimately related to thrush family ''Turdidae'' and Old World flycatcher family ''Muscicapidae''. World: 362 species; Thailand: 58 species. SMALL (9-26 cm), ACTIVE, insectivorous birds with THIN bills adapted for gleaning insects from foliage. Rather drab, with green, olive, brown, buff, and black the predominant colours. Unlike thrushes, have unspotted juvenile plumage. Have THINNER legs than babblers. Many are long-distance migrants. Sexes usually similar. Nests vary from simple cups to domed structures placed in trees, bushes, or grass or hidden in the ground. The tailorbirds (''Orthotomus'') sew leaves together into purse-shaped containers for their nests. Eggs usually speckled . The young are cared for by both parents.<br><br>Distr.: mainly from Europe and Asia to Australia and Africa, but a few in the Americas.', ' ');
