INSERT INTO FAMILY VALUES (NULL, 2,'Carangidae', '718', 'Medium to large sizes. Many genera & species. Body long, elliptic or cylindrical, flat from side to side. Tail end small & strong, with or without small & round scales. Lateral line entire, anterior section more or less curved up. Angled scales cover entire or part of lateral line, some species with angled scales only on tail end. Usually 2 dorsal fins, spines short & weak, sometimes disappear with age. 2nd dorsal fin usually higher than the 1st. Anal fin often similar to 2nd dorsal fin, with II spines. Good swimmers. Habitat: often near surface of warm seas, some move to temperate zones during summer. Many exploited for food, quite high economic value.', ' ');
